  "text": "We took a different approach to genetic determinants of BP variation in the population: harnessing the power of trait extremes [CITATION_1] , coupled with pooling for genome wide association [CITATION_2] . The use of phenotypic extremes is a powerful approach both theoretically and practically [CITATION_3] in genetic association studies, and genomic DNA pooling has been an efficient strategy in genome wide searches for susceptibility alleles. Here we coupled these two strategies, discovering and verifying the role of a novel solute transporter in association with systemic hypertension.",
